{
  "stem": "1895.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we all pitched in and helped my father do anything we could to earn for the sustenance we needed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, because of the position that my father had and because of the fact that he worked for German owners, as I told you before, he was-- we were lucky in a way, because these Germans, even though they were ethnics-- they were German ethnics who lived in Poland even before the war-- they had lived in the town of Radom, the city of Radom for many years.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at first, just like nobody else, they didn't believe that Hitler is for real, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everybody thought that once England and France get into war, they will take care of Hitler in one fell swoop.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, we know now it didn't happen that way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in those days, even the Germans, the ethnic Germans, didn't believe that Hitler was going to make it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They thought it was only temporary.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they wanted to maintain their ties with the Jewish business community that they had before the war so that in case Hitler is gone and the war ends, they would still be able to function in our city.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So things in the first year of occupation, the first year and a half I might say, were not as bad as they could have been.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were able to maintain our family and we did fairly well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had enough to eat, and there was no question of-- of starvation or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But when the Germans conquered France and Paris fell, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the attitude of these German bosses, as well as many other people who are so-called fence-sitters, changed.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
